## 4. The Business Model

### What It Is

Hummingbirds is a two-sided marketplace connecting brands with hyperlocal nano-creators (people with 200-10,000 followers who post about their local community). Brands pay to run campaigns. Creators participate for free in exchange for in-kind perks (gift cards, free experiences, free products). Hummingbirds takes 0% commission from creators.

### The Core Insight

Word of mouth marketing has always been the most trusted form of marketing. Hummingbirds digitises and scales it. Rather than paying one macro-influencer with 500,000 followers to post once, brands activate 20-50 local creators with 500-5,000 followers each — people whose audiences are their actual neighbours, friends and community members.

### Why This Works

- **Local trust:** A creator with 800 followers in a local town has more influence over local buying decisions than a macro-influencer with 200,000 national followers.
- **Engagement rates:** Hummingbirds sees 3-4% average engagement vs 0.7% industry standard — over 5x higher.
- **Retail velocity:** CPG brands using Hummingbirds have seen 4x-14x increases in sales in controlled pilots.
- **UGC value:** Every Reel and Story becomes a brand-owned content asset, repurposable for ads and organic posts.
- **Conversion:** Many creators become paying long-term customers of the brand after campaigns. Some businesses report 80% sustained revenue lift for three months post-campaign.
- **No algorithm required:** Hummingbirds content doesn’t need to go viral. It just needs to reach the right 800 people in the right city.

### What Hummingbirds Is NOT

- Not an influencer agency
- Not a traditional influencer platform (no follower minimums, no cash payments)
- Not a UGC-for-hire service
- Not focused on online or DTC brands (hyperlocal, in-store, place-based behaviour only)

