## 5. How It Works — The Full Mechanism

### Brand Side

**Step 1: Signup & Qualification**

Brands discover Hummingbirds through press, word of mouth, or trade shows (Expo West, Fancy Foods). They fill out a qualification form with: name, company, work email, product category, distribution type, US regions, and retail expansion plans. This form is a deliberate ICP filter. DTC-only brands are a poor fit.

**Step 2: Sales Call**

All brand onboarding is sales-led. There is no self-serve. No pricing page exists on the website. The CTA across all brand-facing pages is ‘Book a Call.’

**Step 3: Campaign Creation**

Once a brand signs, they (or Hummingbirds HQ) create the campaign brief in the admin dashboard. The brief includes:

- Business name and campaign headline
- Target cities and communities
- Content needed (Reel required + Story)
- Content requirements (required tags, hashtags, what must appear)
- Talking points (3 key messages for creators to weave in naturally)
- Inspiration (3-4 specific video concepts with titles and descriptions)
- Campaign dates (open date, expression of interest deadline, content deadline)
- Perk details (gift card value, retailer, how delivered)
- Target number of creators
- Campaign priorities (UGC / Engagements / Brand Awareness / Sales Velocity)

**Step 4: Creator Selection**

Brands review all creators who expressed interest. They can see each creator’s Instagram profile, follower count, content style, completion rate, and any pitch they wrote (the ‘bird blurb’). Brands handpick the creators they want.

**Step 5: Content & Analytics**

Selected creators post their content. The platform automatically pulls engagement data via the Instagram API (reach, likes, comments, views). The brand dashboard shows real-time analytics across all creators.

### Creator Side

**Onboarding Flow**

1. Visit app.hummingbirds.com on mobile browser (web app, not native app)
1. Select city from dropdown
1. Upload profile pic, enter date of birth, gender, phone number (SMS required for campaign notifications), optional mailing address
1. Connect Instagram — OAuth integration requests: View profile, Access and manage comments, Access and manage insights. All three permissions required.
1. Welcome screen — ‘How It Works’: I’m Interested → Confirm Partnership → Upload Content → Earn real world perks
1. Access the Discover feed

**The Campaign Flow**

Creators browse the Discover feed — campaign cards showing brand name, campaign headline, perk value, and campaign dates. Tapping a card reveals the full brief with six accordion sections: About The Brand, Perk Details, About The Campaign, Content Requirements, Talking Points, Inspiration.

Creators tap ‘I’m Interested’. They can write a pitch explaining why they’re a good fit. The brand reviews and selects. Selected creators are notified by email and SMS. They confirm their spot, receive the perk, create content, post it, and upload the post link to the platform.

**The Completion Rate System**

Every creator has a visible completion rate — the percentage of confirmed campaigns they’ve fully completed. Brands can see this when reviewing applicants. High completion rate = more campaign opportunities. Ghost a campaign = lower completion rate = fewer future selections.

**The Two Campaign Types**

- **Brand Campaigns:** Paid by brands. Specific creator count, specific perk, specific requirements. Creators apply, brand selects, guaranteed perk upon completion.
- **Community Campaigns:** Run by Hummingbirds HQ, not brands. No specific brand required. Creators post about any relevant brand (e.g. any local coffee shop on National Coffee Day). Entry for prize draw. These keep the community active between paid campaigns.

**The Charm — The Creator Community**

Completing your first campaign unlocks access to The Charm — Hummingbirds’ private creator community. ‘Complete your first campaign to join 2,000+ authentic creators.’ The Charm hosts events, creator meetups, peer support, and brand discovery. It is the retention flywheel.

**The Referrals Feature**

In the More menu, creators can access a referrals programme. They can invite friends to join Hummingbirds. Peer referral is Hummingbirds’ primary organic growth mechanism for creator supply.

