## 6. Pricing

### Brand Pricing — Never Publicly Disclosed

Hummingbirds has never published pricing. No pricing page exists. All brand onboarding requires a sales call.

### What Is Known

- Credit-based pricing — brands buy credits that provide access to the platform and fund campaigns
- 0% commission from creators — brands fund all creator perks directly
- Creator perks range from $15 to over $800 depending on product/experience value
- Most perks are approximately $50 (gift card value)
- Gift cards delivered via Whistle — virtual prepaid Visa cards sent by email link
- Brands pay a platform fee to launch campaigns on top of creator perk costs

### Reverse-Engineered Estimates

From public data: approaching $1M ARR in late 2023 with ~50-100 brand partners = $10,000-20,000 average annual brand spend. A 20-creator campaign at $50 gift cards each = $1,000 in creator costs alone. Platform fee estimated at $1,500-$2,500 per campaign. Total brand spend per campaign estimated at $2,500-$3,500. Brands running 5-8 campaigns per year = $12,500-$28,000 annual spend per brand.

### Creator Compensation — Always In-Kind

Creators are NEVER paid cash. This is a deliberate and fundamental design decision. Perks are always in-kind: gift cards, complimentary experiences, free merchandise, or event tickets.

> Why no cash? Cash changes the creator relationship from community to transaction. Cash creators evaluate campaigns by hourly rate, compare platforms, and lose authentic enthusiasm. In-kind perks attract genuine lifestyle creators who want the experience, not income optimisers. This preserves content authenticity which is the entire value proposition.

